column3: A decision made by experienced policy makers from both viewpoints, who have dealt with difficult bills in the past.
column4: in-favor and opposed, for politicians of high amount (in years) of political experience

column3: I hope that the committee will be able to oppose and reject the bill, but tried to make the committee as least controversial as possible.
column4: I wanted a balanced set of people in the committee, so an equal amount of people that were in the same party, male and female representation, and equal amount of people opposed or in favor of banning abortion.

column3: I want abortion to be allowed if the case called for it, such as rape. Otherwise, I want the baby's life to be prtotected. BUT sending to prison is too much so no to prison.
column4: I wanted a diverse group of people because america is diverse

column3: My hope would be that the committee could debate by presenting differing views, and come to a consensus about the bill. If a consensus wasn't possible, I would expect a modification to the bill that meets midway.
column4: I wanted there to be a greater representation of women in the committee, so I decided on having 6 women and 4 men. Then, I put in a maximum age filter to 65, so that people of similar age groups could debate more productively. I mapped the y-axis to political experience, and x-axis to the party. I then used the filter on whether they were opposed to the bill or not, to make a homogenous mix of candidates.

Considered every politician in the design space, chose two final metrics based on religion and career. Other consideration was age because of difference in opinions in generations. tried to have a representative from at least on religion affiliation and one career choice

column3: to stop the ban on abortion
column4: I wanted people first of all who opposed the ban, as I do. I also wanted people knowledgeable about the issue, and I feel like that includes doctors and scientists. I wanted a range of ages, but no one super old because I feel like the world is so much different now than when they were growing up, we need people who know the current age-- younger people. I also wanted to make sure some other religions were represented, and that there was a spread of men and women.

column3: I want the committee to choose a result that would represent the opinions of US citizen. However, I also want that they make a choice that can be most beneficial for the one who are affected most by the bills ( women ) and that the choice takes women health into considerations.
column4: Occupations should be doctors, lawyers, career politician. Age should be from 40 to 60. Equally opiniated between banning and not banning
